
















<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial">Hey all,</span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial">Our next version of the Ushahidi platform is
here with us, 2.6 code-named Tripoli. As a follow up to an email by @rjmackay
and myself before the code- freeze, there have been several improvements on the
platform and so we request you to upgrade your deployments or grab this new
version and give it a spin. As always we love feedback and in case there are
any issues with upgrade or installation, hit us up on the dev chat. For any
code – related issues i.e bugs/features – put them up on <a href="https://github.com/ushahidi/Ushahidi_Web/issues?milestone=&amp;page=1&amp;state=open">github issues</a> on the
Ushahidi_Web repository.</span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial">Enjoy 2.6</span></p>

